Package polyglot.frontend.goals

This package defines goals that the compiler attempts to complete by scheduling compiler passes in accordance with their dependencies.
See Also:
Goal, AbstractGoal
  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    EndGoal
    The EndGoal interface is used to tag the last goal for a job.
    Goal
    A goal abstractly represents something that the compiler is supposed to achieve by automatically scheduling passes.
  • Class Summary

    AbstractGoal
    An AbstractGoal is the base class of most Goal implementations.
    Barrier
    A Barrier goal synchronizes all the jobs to reach the same goal.
